            "patch": {
                "description": "Update information of an existing task in the system\n### Field update logic (Three-state logic):\n1. *Field not provided*: `description` is ignored, database value does not change\n2. *Value explicitly provided*: `\"description\": \"Buy milk and bread at the store\"` – sets new description in DB\n3. *Null explicitly provided*: `\"description\": null` – clears the field in DB (sets to NULL)\nRestrictions: `title` and `completed` cannot be set to null",
                "consumes": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "produces": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "tags": [
                    "tasks"
                ],
                "summary": "Update task",
                "parameters": [
                    {
                        "type": "integer",
                        "description": "ID of the task to update",
                        "name": "id",
                        "in": "path",
                        "required": true
                    },
                    {
                        "description": "Patch task request body",
                        "name": "request",
                        "in": "body",
                        "required": true,
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/internal_features_tasks_transport_http.PatchTaskRequest"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "responses": {
                    "200": {
                        "description": "Task successfully updated",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/internal_features_tasks_transport_http.PatchUserResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "400": {
                        "description": "Bad request",
                        "schema": {
